{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 30''' is the 30th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
As with all other days 30 of the Sino-Japanese calendar it sometimes happens and sometimes does not depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Months are also annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big}} for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small}} for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|ja|孝徳天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[585]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A Buddhist proponent, {{ill|Mononobe no Moriya|ja|物部守屋|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, who opposed Buddhism, set fire to Buddhist images and temples. == Births ==
== Deaths == * [[Kayū|嘉祐]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1063]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Renzong of Song|ja|仁宗|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 4th Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[1010]]).
